org.digijava.kernel.ampapi.endpoints.activity

Class SimpleFieldAccessor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.digijava.kernel.ampapi.endpoints.activity.SimpleFieldAccessor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FieldAccessor

    public class SimpleFieldAccessor
extends java.lang.Object
implements FieldAccessor
    Treats collections as values. In order to edit a collection one has to retrieve the collection, edit it, then write the collection back. Collections as values are necessary because in DiscriminatedFieldAccessor we would need to implement a collection wrapper that can iterate/manipulate the wrapped collection on the fly.
